[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":349},["ShallowReactive",2],{"api/learn-center-post-en-what-is-an-ethereum-etf-investing-in-ethereum-simplified":3,"footer-en":74,"learn/cryptocurrency-guide/what-is-an-ethereum-etf-investing-in-ethereum-simplified-en-seo":257,"navigation-en-learn-center":262,"api/learn-categories-en":306},{"seo":4,"locale":20,"breadcrumbs":21,"excerpt":29,"featuredImage":30,"components":37,"title":5,"formattedPublishedAt":49,"geofencings":50,"category":51,"pagination":53,"campaignExternalId":7,"cta":56},{"title":5,"metaTitle":5,"metaDescription":6,"keywords":7,"metaRobots":7,"structuredData":8,"metaImage":9,"metaSocial":16,"canonicalURL":7,"localizations":17},"What Is an Ethereum ETF? Investing in Ethereum Simplified","Ethereum ETFs: Financial instruments allowing traditional investors to gain exposure to Ethereum without directly purchasing the cryptocurrency.",null,{},{"url":10,"mime":11,"ext":12,"width":13,"height":14,"name":15,"alt":7},"bitstampImageUrl/what_is_an_ethereum_etf_investing_in_ethereum_simplified_e48bf0f0db.png","image/png",".png",900,451,"what is an ethereum etf investing in ethereum simplified.png",[],[18],{"pathname":19,"locale":20},"/learn/cryptocurrency-guide/what-is-an-ethereum-etf-investing-in-ethereum-simplified/","en",[22,26],{"id":23,"text":24,"url":23,"asUrl":25},"/learn/cryptocurrency-guide/","Cryptocurrency guide",true,{"id":27,"text":5,"url":19,"asUrl":28},"what-is-an-ethereum-etf-investing-in-ethereum-simplified",false,"\u003Cp>Ethereum exchange-traded funds (ETFs) are a financial instrument that give traditional market investors the ability to invest in cryptocurrency without having to directly purchase the asset. \u003C/p>\n",{"url":31,"mime":32,"ext":33,"width":34,"height":35,"name":36,"alt":7},"bitstampImageUrl/what_is_an_ethereum_etf_investing_in_ethereum_simplified_9ac74b8151.svg","image/svg+xml",".svg",1920,1080,"what is an ethereum etf investing in ethereum simplified.svg",[38],{"component":39,"props":40,"content":41,"secondaryContent":45,"ctas":47,"secondaryCtas":48,"ctasNoMarginTop":28},"section.full-text",{"centered":28,"withoutSectionContainer":28},{"text":42,"width":43,"align":44},"\u003Cp>The Ethereum blockchain was the first to support smart contracts, making it the first hub for hosting decentralized applications (Dapps). As its popularity continues to rise, more investors are seeking ways to invest in its underlying asset, ETH.  \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>ETFs are investment funds managed by financial companies like BlackRock that trade on major exchanges like NYSE or Nasdaq. These funds come with management fees but provide exposure to diverse assets, from broad market indexes to commodities, and may even offer amplified returns (and risks) using leverage.  \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Ethereum ETFs might offer more peace of mind to traders that wish to trade the asset within the regulated framework of the stock market. Further, Ethereum ETFs offer a familiar way for long-term investors to diversify their portfolio by adding exposure to the crypto market without the complexities of directly purchasing Ethereum. \u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2>How do Ethereum ETFs work?\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Ethereum ETFs, like traditional ETFs, are investment funds traded on stock exchanges and are tied to the performance of the underlying asset, ETH.  \u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3>Futures ETFs\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Futures-based ETFs track the price of Ethereum futures contracts, which are agreements to buy or sell ETH at a specific price on a future date. Importantly, these ETFs hold derivatives contracts and do not directly hold the Ethereum asset. \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Because they are a more speculative asset, futures contract prices can deviate from the actual spot price of ETH, leading to potential tracking errors.  \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The first Ethereum Futures ETFs were listed in the US in October 2023. \u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3>Spot ETFs\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Spot Ethereum ETFs are financial instruments that directly reflect the price of ETH. Issuers like BlackRock and Fidelity purchase and hold actual ETH, and ETF shareholders essentially own a portion of these ETH holdings. This direct ownership model, combined with the ability to create and redeem ETF shares, ensures the ETF's price closely mirrors Ethereum's market value.    \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>On July 23, 2024, several spot Ethereum ETFs were approved and started trading on major U.S. exchanges.  \u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2>Benefits and Risks of Investing in Ethereum ETFs\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>As with any investment, investing in Ethereum ETFs, both spot and futures-based ones, can come with different advantages and risks. \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Benefits of investing in Ethereum ETFs include: \u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Accessibility  – Investors can purchase ETH using their brokerage account, which removes a lot of the complexities of buying, storing and managing the asset directly. \u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Diversification  – Traditional investors can now gain exposure to the crypto market by adding ETH ETFs to their portfolio.  \u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Regulation  – Ethereum ETFs are traded on traditional stock exchanges that are subject to more regulatory scrutiny, providing investors with more protection and transparency.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>The cryptocurrency market can be different from the traditional markets, and carry certain risks for investors to consider: \u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Volatility  – The crypto market can be highly volatile, and the price fluctuations of the underlying asset will be reflected in the ETF’s price. \u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Fees  – ETFs charge management fees to cover their operational costs and might eat into an investor’s return.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Ch2>Ethereum ETF Essentials\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Ethereum ETFs offer investors a simplified and regulated way to gain exposure to Ethereum's price movements without directly owning the cryptocurrency, providing benefits like accessibility and portfolio diversification. \u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>There are two main types of Ethereum ETFs: futures-based ETFs, which track the price of Ethereum futures contracts, and spot ETFs, which directly hold Ethereum. \u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>While Ethereum ETFs present attractive investment opportunities, they also carry risks, including the inherent volatility of the crypto market and potential tracking errors for futures-based ETFs. Additionally, investors should consider the impact of management fees on their long-term returns.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n","full","left",{"text":46},"",[],[],"November 1st, 2024",{},{"title":24,"url":23,"geofencings":52},{"geofencing-uk":25},{"previous":54,"next":55},"/learn/cryptocurrency-guide/what-is-algorand-algo/","/learn/cryptocurrency-guide/what-is-apecoin-ape/",{"component":39,"props":57,"content":62,"secondaryContent":65,"ctas":66,"secondaryCtas":73,"ctasNoMarginTop":28},{"sectionId":7,"backgroundColor":58,"paddingTop":59,"paddingBottom":59,"ordering":7,"ratio":60,"centered":28,"containerSize":61,"withoutSectionContainer":28},"Crypto lime","medium","1:1","normal",{"text":63,"width":43,"align":64},"\u003Ch2>\u003Cmark>Ready\u003C/mark> to start your crypto journey?\u003C/h2>\n","center",{"text":46},[67],{"text":68,"url":69,"external":28,"noFollow":25,"type":70,"openModal":7,"downloadItem":71},"Getting Started","/onboarding/register/","Button - Primary",{"file":72},{},[],{"ready":25,"sections":75,"disclaimer":255,"copyright":256},[76,119,142,165,197,216],{"title":77,"content":46,"items":78},"About",[79,84,89,94,99,104,109,114],{"noFollow":25,"isExternal":28,"name":80,"value":81,"isEmail":28,"isPhoneNumber":28,"isText":28,"showOnDesktop":25,"showOnMobile":25,"attachment":82,"geofencings":83},"Who We Are","/about-us/",{},{},{"noFollow":28,"isExternal":28,"name":85,"value":86,"isEmail":28,"isPhoneNumber":28,"isText":28,"showOnDesktop":25,"showOnMobile":25,"attachment":87,"geofencings":88},"The Bitstamp Way","/bitstamp-way/",{},{},{"noFollow":25,"i